 21219	/// which enables exact analytic gradients.
 21220	///
 21221	/// # Mathematical Background
 21222	/// For B-splines, a linear function f(x) = a + bx has coefficients c_j = a + b·G_j
 21223	/// where G_j are the Greville abscissae. Therefore, constraining the coefficient
 21224	/// vector θ to satisfy:
 21225	///   - Σ θ_j = 0  (orthogonal to constants)
 21226	///   - Σ θ_j·G_j = 0  (orthogonal to linear in Greville coordinates)
 21227	/// removes the ability to represent any linear function.
 21228	///
 21229	/// # Arguments
 21230	/// * `knot_vector` - Full knot vector
 21231	/// * `degree` - B-spline degree
 21232	/// * `penalty_order` - Order of difference penalty (typically 2)
