 14064	// Wahba/Sobolev kernel on S²
 14065	// ============================================================================
 14066	//
 14067	// `K_m^{Sobolev}(γ) = (1/4π) · Σ_{l ≥ 1} (2l + 1) · [l(l + 1)]^{-m} · P_l(cos γ)`
 14068	//
 14069	// is the reproducing kernel of the canonical Sobolev space `H^m(S²)` with
 14070	// the inner product `⟨f, g⟩ = Σ_l [l(l+1)]^m · f̂_l · ĝ_l`.
 14071	//
 14072	// For `m ∈ {1, 2, 3}` we use the closed-form expressions derived in
 14073	// Beatson & zu Castell, "Thinplate Splines on the Sphere", SIGMA 14 (2018)
 14074	// 083 (Section 6.2). In their notation `u = (1 − cos γ)/2 = sin²(γ/2)`:
 14075	//
 14076	//   k_{3,1}(x) =  −ln(u)  − 1
 14077	//   k_{3,2}(x) =   Li_2(1 − u) + 1 − π²/6
 14078	//   k_{3,3}(x) = −2 Li_3(u) − Li_2(1 − u) + ln(u) · Li_2(u)
 14079	//                 + 2 ζ(3) + π²/6 − 2
 14080	//
 14081	// Beatson & zu Castell normalize so that the kernel is for the
 14082	// `[f, g] = (1/σ_d) ∫ f g dσ` inner product (their eq. 3.2), i.e. surface
 14083	// measure normalized to one. The basis pipeline here uses the
 14084	// (1/4π)-scaled reproducing kernel (kernel for plain `∫ f g dσ`), so we
 14085	// divide their expressions by `4π`.
 14086	//
 14087	// For `m = 4` no published elementary-plus-Li₄ form exists; we fall back
 14088	// to the truncated spectral Legendre series (96 terms, error ≲ 1e-12).
 14089	
